<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-26T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-26T14:00:00-05:00" n="39" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d39">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/152a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-26T14:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 6, 1916, 2 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3062. Berlin press dispatch dated May 26 quotes you as having given
                            interview with Munich newspaper on favorable prospects of peace. Berlin
                            dispatch dated June 3 reports interview with evening <hi rend="italic">National Zeitung</hi> on same subject. Department assumes that
                            these reports are mere inventions, but would be glad to have some
                            statement from you to this effect in order that interviews may be
                            officially denied here.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>